When to Use CRM Analytics Direct Data for Snowflake

To run analysis on your Snowflake data, you can use CRM Analytics Direct Data for Snowflake or Snowflake input connectors or a combination of the two.

Refer to these guidelines to determine whether Direct Data for Snowflake meets your business needs.

With Direct Data for Snowflake, you can:

Save time on setup and eliminate the need for data syncs, dataflows, or recipes.
Eliminate the need to load and prepare large volumes of Snowflake data into CRM Analytics and manage its dataflows.
Free up data pipelines for resources and processes that require them.
Get real-time metrics in dashboards and lenses with queries based on Snowflake data.
Meet data residency requirements on Snowflake data but still analyze it to make business decisions.
Maintain on-demand access to less frequently used data, such as order details.
Incorporate data from Snowflake Data Marketplace for deeper insights on your Snowflake data.
Take advantage of Snowflakeâ€™s native support for analytics on semi-structured data formats, such as JSON, Parquet, or XML.
Quickly create and test which data models to use with your Snowflake data before connecting it to CRM Analytics. You can even collaborate easily with other users during this process.
